8) Development Tech Plan (Detailed)
8.1 Reference Architecture (Cloud-native, multi-tenant)
[Client Admin UI] --(HTTPS)--> [API Gateway] --> [Auth (SSO/OAuth2)]
                                       |
                                       v
                              [Orchestration Service]
   |----> [Messaging Adapter (WhatsApp Cloud API/BSP SDK)]
   |----> [Template Service + Policy Engine]
   |----> [Conversation Window Tracker (24h/72h)]
   |----> [AI Assist (LLM + Retrieval)]
   |----> [Segmentation & Send-Time Optimization]
   |----> [Commerce & Payments (Razorpay/PayU)]
   |----> [Analytics & Attribution]
   |----> [Webhook Ingest (events)]
                                       |
                                       v
                            [Event Bus / Stream (Kafka)]
                                       |
                     +-----------------+-----------------+
                     |                                   |
            [OLTP DB - Postgres]                 [Data Lake - S3/ADLS]
                     |                                   |
            [Cache - Redis]                    [Warehouse - BigQuery/Snowflake]
                     |                                   |
            [Search - OpenSearch]             [BI/Reporting - Metabase/Superset]
Key choices & why:
â€¢	Messaging adapter: Use WhatsApp Cloud API first; add BSP-specific adapters (Gupshup/Infobip/Twilio) for throughput or enterprise features. Keeps you portable across providers. [wss.gupshup.io], [twilio.com]
â€¢	Event-driven: WhatsApp is conversational; an event bus (Kafka) makes retries, escalations, and analytics easier.
â€¢	Data: Postgres for tenants/conversations/templates; Redis for rate limiting & windows; Warehouse for cohort analytics & attribution.
â€¢	AI: Bring your own LLM (Azure OpenAI/Bedrock/Vertex) + retrieval (FAQs, product catalog).
â€¢	Search: OpenSearch for fast lookups on contacts, orders, sessions.
â€¢	Security: VPC, WAF, API keys per tenant, RBAC, KMS-backed encryption.
