8.4 Policy Linter (Utility vs Marketing) â€“ Pseudocode
Python
def classify_template(body:str, buttons:list, context:dict)->str:
"""
Enforce July 1, 2025 guideline: Utility templates must be strictly non-promotional.
Returns: 'utility' or 'marketing'
"""
promo_terms = {"discount", "offer", "sale", "limited time", "coupon", "deal", "save", "buy now", "shop"}
# Heuristics: any promotional intent -> marketing
text = body.lower()
if any(term in text for term in promo_terms):
return "marketing"
# Buttons encouraging purchase are promotional
for b in buttons or []:
if b.get("type") == "url" and ("offer" in b.get("title","").lower() or "shop" in b.get("title","").lower()):
return "marketing"
# Utility must be transactional: order/status/appointment/account alerts
if context.get("trigger") in {"order_update","shipping_update","appointment_reminder","invoice","payment_receipt","account_alert"}:
return "utility"
# Default fallback: marketing to avoid policy violations
return "marketing"
Show more lines
Keep a rules + ML ensemble; err on marketing when ambiguous to avoid policy violations, consistent with stricter reclassification guidance. [ycloud.com]
8.5 Conversation Costing (Per-message; free windows)
Python
def compute_cost(msg, rate_card):
"""
msg: {category, country, sent_at, is_template, within_24h_service, within_ctwa_72h}
rate_card: dict[country][category] -> price_in_inr
"""
if not msg["is_template"]:
return 0.0 # free-form reply in service window
# Utility inside 24h service window: free
if msg["category"] == "utility" and msg["within_24h_service"]:
return 0.0
# Any template within CTWA 72h free window: free
if msg["within_ctwa_72h"]:
return 0.0
# Otherwise charge per destination country & category
return rate_card[msg["country"]][msg["category"]]
Show more lines
Mirrors per message rules, 24h service window, and 72h CTWA free window dynamics. [linkmobility.com]
